merecat (2.32) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release:
    - Support for HTTPS, self-signed certs and Let's Encrypt.  Works with
      all features, including virtual hosts
    - Support for running HTTP and HTTPS servers from one Merecat daemon
    - Support for SSI, pattern matching to .shtml files
    - Support for PHP, using php-cgi
    - Support for HTTP/1.1 Keep-alive
    - Support for HTTP redirect, to redirect from HTTP to HTTPS
    - Support for server location directive, similar to nginx
    - Added support for HTTP gzip compression, serves .gz files
    - Skip .htpasswd (and .htaccess) in dir listings
    - Allow SO_REUSEPORT, useful for load balancing
    - Fix issue with leading double slash in URL, reported by Steve Kemp
    - Fix issue with receiving a 403 page instead of 404 (no-symlink-check)
    - Fix issue with HTML entities in directory listings
    - Fix merecat.conf: commented out settings should be daemon defaults
    - Built-in icons for FTP dir listings; folder, file, etc.
    - Cute cat faviocon added
    - Portability fixes

 -- Joachim Nilsson <troglobit@gmail.com>  Tue, 07 Jul 2020 09:32:33 +0200

